raw._content: TYNDALL AIR FORCE BASE, Fla. (AFIE) -- The camera captures Lt. Col. Jerry Kerby, an F-15 Eagle pilot from the 325th Operations Support Squadron at Tyndall, while transient alert tug operators provide a unique filming platform. The Navy had its phenomenal big-screen hit “Top Gun.” Now it’s the Air Force’s turn -- at least on the small screens of America. After nearly two years of serving as a major filming location, the Tyndall Air Force Base mission is about to fly with full afterburners into the living rooms of nearly 19 million television viewers across America. Titled “American Fighter Pilots,” CBS signed on for eight one-hour episodes of the reality-based series that intimately follows the on- and off-duty lives of three students as they train to become F-15 pilots. Scheduled for a late-January launch, the series also features in-depth interviews with the instructor pilots. (U.S. Air Force photo by Staff Sgt. Dan Neely)
